# Project Structure and Build Rules

## Project Structure Standards

### Package Structure
```
packages/
├── agents/             # Core agent functionality
├── anthropic/          # Anthropic provider
├── openai/             # OpenAI provider
├── google/             # Google provider
├── sessions/           # Session management
├── team/               # Team collaboration
├── workflow/           # Workflow visualization/events
├── playground/         # Playground UI package
├── remote/             # Remote execution package
├── dag-core/           # DAG domain contracts and state rules
├── dag-runtime/        # DAG orchestration runtime
├── dag-worker/         # DAG worker execution layer
├── dag-scheduler/      # DAG scheduler layer
├── dag-projection/     # DAG projection/read-model layer
├── dag-api/            # DAG API/composition layer
└── dag-designer/       # DAG web designer layer
```

### DAG Dependency Direction (Mandatory)
- `dag-core` is the DAG SSOT contract package.
- `dag-runtime`, `dag-worker`, `dag-scheduler`, `dag-projection`, `dag-api`, and `dag-designer` depend on `dag-core`.
- `dag-designer` must not import runtime/worker/scheduler implementations directly.

### Configuration Files
- **tsconfig.base.json** - Base TypeScript configuration with strict rules
- **.eslintrc.json** - Root ESLint configuration with type safety rules
- Package-specific configs extend the base configuration

### Protected Settings
- TypeScript strict mode settings are immutable
- ESLint type safety rules are error-level and immutable
- Any/unknown type rules cannot be modified

### Development Workflow
- All code must pass strict TypeScript compilation
- Zero tolerance for any/unknown types in production code
- ESLint enforcement at error level for type safety
- This repository is a **pnpm workspace monorepo**. Follow `.cursor/rules/project-structure-rules.mdc`.

### Type System & SSOT (Mandatory)
- **Type naming (I*/T*)**: see `.cursor/rules/type-ssot-rules.mdc`
- **Owner-based SSOT (Option A)**: see `.cursor/rules/type-ssot-rules.mdc`

## pnpm Workspace Monorepo Build Rules

### 🚨 Critical Build Requirements

#### Package Modification → Build Mandatory
- **ANY** modification to files in `packages/*/src/` **REQUIRES** immediate build
- **NEVER** skip builds after code changes in packages
- **ALWAYS** verify build success before proceeding to next steps

### 🚫 Prohibited Practices

- **NEVER** skip builds after package modifications
- **NEVER** commit code that doesn't build successfully  
- **NEVER** use temporary workarounds to make builds pass
- **NEVER** disable TypeScript strict checks to fix builds

### Guidance Location
Build commands and workflow guidance live in the project skill:
`.cursor/skills/pnpm-monorepo-build/SKILL.md`.
